---
Source:
  Title: The Complete Works of Chuang Tzu
  ID: 50ae0a98-5702-40cb-8c11-4c6297aa457a
  Translator: Burton Watson
By: Zhuangzi
Locus:
  Chapter: 8
  Paragraph: 8
Title: Webbed Toes
---
A little confusion can alter the sense of direction; a great confusion
can alter the inborn nature. How do I know this is so? Ever since that
man of the Yu clan began preaching benevolence and righteousness and
stirring up the world, all the men in the world have dashed headlong
for benevolence and righteousness. This is because benevolence and
righteousness have altered their inborn nature, is it not?
